comments: Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the Aylesbury Vale unparished area.

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of Aylesbury. See also Table 2, note 
    (w).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Cholesbury 
    cum St. Leonards.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Buckland, Hawridge, Aston 
    Clinton, Cholesbury and Drayton Beauchamp. See also Table 2, note (m).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish of 
    Wendover. See also Table 2, note (l).

Abolished 1.4.1982 and added to the parish of Slapton. See 
    also Table 2, note (n).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Cholesbury 
    cum St. Leonards. See also Table 2, note (g).

Abolished 1.4.1965 and divided between the parishes of Leighton 
    Linslade and Soulbury. See also Table 2, notes (n) and (u).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish of 
    Towersey. See also Table 2, note (l).
Abolished 25.3.1886 and added to the parish of Quanton.

Transferred from Buckinghamshire to Oxfordshire on 1.4.1933. See 
    also Table 2, notes (i), (j) and (l).

Created 1894 from parts of the parish of Aylesbury (which until 
    25.3.1886 formed detached parts of the parish of Bierton with Broughton) outside 
    Aylesbury Urban District. Abolished 1.10.1896 and added to the parish of 
    Aylesbury.

Created 1894 from parts of the parish of Aylesbury (which until 
    25.3.1886 formed detached parts of the parish of Bierton with Broughton) in 
    Aylesbury Urban District. Abolished 1.10.1896 and added to the parish of 
    Aylesbury.
